<pb facs="nei.j4a.35a.10a.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">10a</fw>
<note type="curatorial"></note>

<fw type="letterheader">Wayne State College
Wayne, Nebraska 68787

WAYNE STATE COLLEGE WAYNE, NEBRASKA M.M.C. 1891-1910 FOUNDED 1910
W.A. Brandenburg
    President
</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>April 14, 1971
</dateline>
<address>
<addrLine>Dr. John G. Neihardt
</addrLine>
<addrLine>5835 Vine Street
</addrLine>
<addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska 68505
</addrLine>
</address>
<salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:
</salute>
</opener>

<p>"Great" is the word for your performance in Wayne. Very many people have told me yours was the greatest commencement "speech" they have heard.</p>
<p>It was gracious of you to permit the filming for our documentary, and to add Black Elk's Prayer later.</p>
<p>All best wishes from your Alma Mater.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Sincerely</salute>
<signed>W. A. Brandenburg (H)</signed>
<note>W. A. Brandenburg</note>
<note>WAB:sat
(Dictated but not read)</note>
</closer>

</div1>
